      "message": "Line 1969: 🟡 Suggestion: Filesystem operations (`std::filesystem::remove`) are performed inside the `editConfig` callback, which likely holds a lock on the account configuration. Disk I/O under a lock can cause latency spikes. Consider moving the file deletion outside of the `editConfig` lambda — capture the paths first, clear the config, then delete the files afterward.",
