      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 1969: 🟡 Suggestion: File I/O operations (`std::filesystem::remove`) are performed inside the `editConfig` callback, which likely holds a configuration lock. Deleting files while holding a lock can introduce latency or deadlock risks if the filesystem blocks. Consider moving the file deletion outside the `editConfig` lambda — capture the paths first, clear them in the config, then delete the files afterward.",
      "revId": "a4444ff90b212d78f781c2565e1d10de02e566d4",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
