      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 1971: 🟡 Suggestion: The `std::error_code ec` is captured but never inspected after each `std::filesystem::remove` call. If the deletion fails (e.g., permission denied), the code silently proceeds, clears the config fields, and resets the identity — leaving orphan files on disk with no indication of failure. Consider at least logging the error.\n```suggestion\n                    std::error_code ec;\n                    if (!conf.tlsPrivateKeyFile.empty()) {\n                        std::filesystem::remove(idPath_ / conf.tlsPrivateKeyFile, ec);\n                        if (ec)\n                            JAMI_WARNING(\"Failed to remove private key file: {}\", ec.message());\n                    }\n                    if (!conf.tlsCertificateFile.empty()) {\n                        std::filesystem::remove(idPath_ / conf.tlsCertificateFile, ec);\n                        if (ec)\n                            JAMI_WARNING(\"Failed to remove certificate file: {}\", ec.message());\n                    }\n```",
